{"rss"=>{"channel"=>{"title"=>"Macleans.ca \u00BB Multimedia", "link"=>[{"href"=>"http://www.macleans.ca/multimedia/feed/", "rel"=>"self", "type"=>"application/rss+xml"}, "http://www.macleans.ca"], "description"=>"Canada's only national weekly current affairs magazine.", "lastBuildDate"=>"Sun, 15 Feb 2015 02:53:31 +0000", "language"=>"en-CA", "updatePeriod"=>"hourly", "updateFrequency"=>"1", "generator"=>"http://wordpress.org/?v=3.5.2", "item"=>[{"title"=>"Maclean\u2019s on the Hill: Eve Adams, measles and the Canadian flag", "link"=>"http://www.macleans.ca/politics/macleans-on-the-hill-eve-adams-measles-and-the-canadian-flag/", "comments"=>["http://www.macleans.ca/politics/macleans-on-the-hill-eve-adams-measles-and-the-canadian-flag/#comments", "5"], "pubDate"=>"Fri, 13 Feb 2015 23:07:21 +0000", "creator"=>"macleans.ca", "category"=>["Multimedia", "Ottawa", "Podcast", "Politics"], "guid"=>{"__content__"=>"http://www.macleans.ca/?p=679845", "isPermaLink"=>"false"}, "description"=>"<p>Still trying to make sense of this week in politics? Listen here. </p><p>The post <a href=\"http://www.macleans.ca/politics/macleans-on-the-hill-eve-adams-measles-and-the-canadian-flag/\">Maclean&#8217;s on the Hill: Eve Adams, measles and the Canadian flag</a> appeared first on <a href=\"http://www.macleans.ca\">Macleans.ca</a>.</p>", "encoded"=>"<span itemprop=\"articleBody\" class=\"entry-content\"><p><a href=\"http://www.macleans.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/ON-THE-HILL.jpg\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-514329\" alt=\"podcast\" src=\"http://www.macleans.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/ON-THE-HILL.jpg\" width=\"1600\" height=\"900\" /></a></p>\n<p>Each week, the <em>Maclean\u2019s</em> politics team and Rogers radio\u2019s Cormac MacSweeney sit down to hash out the week\u2019s news in Ottawa.\u00A0This week, we talk to Liberal MP John McCallum about his new caucus colleague, Eve Adams; we ask Canada&#8217;s chief public health officer about measles outbreaks and the anti-vaxxer movement; and we look back at the creation of the Canadian flag with one of the men who helped design it.</p>\n<p>Listen to this week&#8217;s podcast: </p>\n<p><iframe width=\"100%\" height=\"166\" scrolling=\"no\" frameborder=\"no\" src=\"https://w.soundcloud.com/player/?url=https%3A//api.soundcloud.com/tracks/191013689&amp;color=ff5500&amp;auto_play=false&amp;hide_related=false&amp;show_comments=true&amp;show_user=true&amp;show_reposts=false\"></iframe></p>\n<h1 style=\"text-align: center;\">THE HEADLINES</h1>\n<ul class=\"block-grid mobile two-up\">\n<li>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-679883\" alt=\"\" src=\"http://www.macleans.ca/wp-content/uploads/2015/02/adams-thumbnail.jpg\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" /><br />\n<a href=\"http://www.macleans.ca/news/canada/all-about-eve-and-suddenly-steve/\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>On Eve Adams</strong></a><br />\n<em style=\"line-height: 19px;\">What&#8217;s it say about Trudeau?</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-679885\" alt=\"\" src=\"http://www.macleans.ca/wp-content/uploads/2015/02/trudeau-thumbnail.jpg\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" /><br />\n<a href=\"http://www.macleans.ca/politics/ottawa/trudeau-says-tory-defector-eve-adams-must-prove-herself/\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>On Trudeau</strong></a><br />\n<em style=\"line-height: 19px;\">Says it&#8217;s up to Adams</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-678253\" alt=\"\" src=\"http://www.macleans.ca/wp-content/uploads/2015/02/MAC07_VACCINES_THUMBNAIL.jpg\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" /><br />\n<a href=\"http://www.macleans.ca/society/health/the-real-vaccine-scandal/\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>On vaccines</strong></a><br />\n<em style=\"line-height: 19px;\">What&#8217;s really gone wrong?</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-675977\" alt=\"\" src=\"http://www.macleans.ca/wp-content/uploads/2015/02/MAC07_FLAG_FEATURE.jpg\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" /><br />\n<a href=\"http://www.macleans.ca/politics/ottawa/our-flag-as-a-piece-of-modern-design/\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>On the flag</strong></a><br />\n<em style=\"line-height: 19px;\">The excellence of design</em></p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p><a href=\"http://www.macleans.ca/wp-content/uploads/2015/02/episode51.mp3\">Download the podcast here. </a></p>\n</span><p>The post <a href=\"http://www.macleans.ca/politics/macleans-on-the-hill-eve-adams-measles-and-the-canadian-flag/\">Maclean&#8217;s on the Hill: Eve Adams, measles and the Canadian flag</a> appeared first on <a href=\"http://www.macleans.ca\">Macleans.ca</a>.</p>", "commentRss"=>"http://www.macleans.ca/politics/macleans-on-the-hill-eve-adams-measles-and-the-canadian-flag/feed/"}, {"title"=>"Introducing The Thrill: Maclean\u2019s pop culture podcast", "link"=>"http://www.macleans.ca/culture/arts/introducing-the-thrill-macleans-pop-culture-podcast/", "comments"=>["http://www.macleans.ca/culture/arts/introducing-the-thrill-macleans-pop-culture-podcast/#comments", "0"], "pubDate"=>"Fri, 13 Feb 2015 20:33:51 +0000", "creator"=>"macleans.ca", "category"=>["Arts", "Multimedia", "Podcast", "The Thrill Podcast"], "guid"=>{"__content__"=>"http://www.macleans.ca/?p=679657", "isPermaLink"=>"false"}, "description"=>"<p>The Maclean's pop culture podcast kicks off with discussion on Fresh Off The Boat and the To Kill A Mockingbird sequel</p><p>The post <a href=\"http://www.macleans.ca/culture/arts/introducing-the-thrill-macleans-pop-culture-podcast/\">Introducing The Thrill: Maclean&#8217;s pop culture podcast</a> appeared first on <a href=\"http://www.macleans.ca\">Macleans.ca</a>.</p>", "encoded"=>"<span itemprop=\"articleBody\" class=\"entry-content\"><div id=\"attachment_679819\" class=\"wp-caption aligncenter\" style=\"width: 1034px\"><img class=\"size-large wp-image-679819\" alt=\"CAROUSEL_THE THRILL\" src=\"http://www.macleans.ca/wp-content/uploads/2015/02/CAROUSEL_THE-THRILL-1024x576.jpg\" width=\"1024\" height=\"576\" /><p class=\"wp-caption-text\">Photograph by May Truong</p></div>\n<p>Looking for thoughtful analysis and friendly banter to navigate the pop culture waters? Have no fear: Maclean&#8217;s The Thrill pop culture podcast is here! Every week, <em>Maclean&#8217;s</em> arts writers Adrian Lee, Emma Teitel and Julia De Laurentiis Johnson will gather to discuss and break down the hottest topics in TV, film, books and music. Expect discussion, analysis, and interviews, all replicating the feeling of having a coffee and chatting with your friends!</p>\n<p>On this week&#8217;s podcast we discuss the ABC sitcom <em>Fresh Off the Boat</em>, which stars an Asian-American family for the first time in two decades;\u00A0the controversial <em>To Kill a Mockingbird</em> sequel from Harper Lee; and, because we&#8217;re starting the show on the eve of Valentine&#8217;s Day, we riff on our favourite love stories in pop culture: what works, what doesn&#8217;t, and why?</p>\n<p>Click the Soundcloud player below to listen. We will be on iTunes soon!</p>\n<p><iframe src=\"https://w.soundcloud.com/player/?url=https%3A//api.soundcloud.com/tracks/190987454&amp;color=ff5500&amp;auto_play=false&amp;hide_related=false&amp;show_comments=true&amp;show_user=true&amp;show_reposts=false\" height=\"166\" width=\"100%\" frameborder=\"no\" scrolling=\"no\"></iframe></p>\n<h1 style=\"text-align: center;\">RELATED STORIES</h1>\n<ul class=\"block-grid mobile two-up\">\n<li>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://www.macleans.ca/culture/television/why-fresh-off-the-boat-may-wind-up-to-be-a-noble-failure/\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://www.macleans.ca/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/MAC07_FOB_FEATURE.jpg\" width=\"100%\" /> <strong>ON FRESH OFF THE BOAT</strong></a><br />\n<em style=\"line-height: 19px;\">Is ABC&#8217;s new sitcom doomed?</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://www.macleans.ca/culture/books/will-harper-lees-new-mockingbird-sing/\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://www.macleans.ca/wp-content/uploads/2015/02/MAC07_HARPER_LEE_THUMBNAIL.jpg\" width=\"100%\" /> <strong>ON A MOCKINGBIRD SEQUEL</strong></a><br />\n<em style=\"line-height: 19px;\">Brian Bethune on whether Harper Lee&#8217;s new <em>Mockingbird</em> will sing</em></p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p><a href=\"http://www.macleans.ca/wp-content/uploads/2015/02/Thrillpodcast01.mp3\"><br />\nDownload this podcast. </a></p>\n</span><p>The post <a href=\"http://www.macleans.ca/culture/arts/introducing-the-thrill-macleans-pop-culture-podcast/\">Introducing The Thrill: Maclean&#8217;s pop culture podcast</a> appeared first on <a href=\"http://www.macleans.ca\">Macleans.ca</a>.</p>", "commentRss"=>"http://www.macleans.ca/culture/arts/introducing-the-thrill-macleans-pop-culture-podcast/feed/"}, {"title"=>"Photo gallery: World Press Photo winners", "link"=>"http://www.macleans.ca/multimedia/photo/photo-gallery-world-press-photo-winners/", "comments"=>["http://www.macleans.ca/multimedia/photo/photo-gallery-world-press-photo-winners/#comments", "0"], "pubDate"=>"Thu, 12 Feb 2015 22:04:56 +0000", "creator"=>"macleans.ca", "category"=>["Photo", "World Press Photo"], "guid"=>{"__content__"=>"http://www.macleans.ca/?p=679323", "isPermaLink"=>"false"}, "description"=>"<p>The prestigious contest showcases the best of photography from 2014</p><p>The post <a href=\"http://www.macleans.ca/multimedia/photo/photo-gallery-world-press-photo-winners/\">Photo gallery: World Press Photo winners</a> appeared first on <a href=\"http://www.macleans.ca\">Macleans.ca</a>.</p>", "encoded"=>"<span itemprop=\"articleBody\" class=\"entry-content\"><p>The World Press Photo Contest may be the most prestigious and popular of its kind\u2014once again, the number of images submitted to more than 97,000, from 5,692 press photographers from 131 countries across the globe. And as if to underscore that, this year also included a new category to add to its exclusive few, Long-Term Projects, which earned more than 14,000 photo submissions just on its own.</p>\n<p>Here are some of the finest photos from this year&#8217;s winning crop, including\u00A0Mads Nissen&#8217;s stunning shot of two gay men in Russia, the picture chosen as the Photo of the Year. These award-winning photos\u00A0will now be touring the world as part of an exhibit.\u00A0For an overview of all the winners,\u00A0<a href=\" http://www.worldpressphoto.org/awards/2015\" target=\"_blank\">click here</a>\u00A0to\u00A0visit the 2015 Contest gallery.</p>\n<script type='text/javascript'>var image_max_height = \"500\";</script><script type='text/javascript'>var imagesArray = [{\"id\":679209,\"mlpId\":\"6587\",\"src\":\"http:\\/\\/www.macleans.ca\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2015\\/02\\/01_Mads-Nissen-660x439.jpg\",\"width\":660,\"height\":439,\"medSrc\":\"http:\\/\\/www.macleans.ca\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2015\\/02\\/01_Mads-Nissen-150x150.jpg\",\"medWidth\":150,\"medHeight\":150,\"smallSrc\":\"http:\\/\\/www.macleans.ca\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2015\\/02\\/01_Mads-Nissen-150x150.jpg\",\"smallWidth\":150,\"smallHeight\":150,\"tagSlugs\":\"\",\"tagNames\":\"\",\"title\":\"World Press Photo of the Year 2014, First Prize Contemporary Issues, Singles\",\"caption\":\"\",\"loaded\":false,\"description\":\"<p>Jon and Alex, a gay couple, during an intimate moment. Life for LGBT people is becoming increasingly difficult in Russia. Sexual minorities face legal and social discrimination, harassment, and even violent hate-crime attacks from religious and nationalistic groups. (Mads Nissen<b>, <\\/b>Denmark, Scanpix\\/Panos Pictures. Shot in St. Petersburg, Russia.)<\\/p>\",\"order\":\"1\",\"imageCount\":\"19\",\"alt\":\"\"}];</script><a name='gallery_top' id='gallery_top'></a><a name='mobile_gallery_top' id='mobile_gallery_top'></a>\n<div id='mlp_ajax_loader'><img src='http://www.macleans.ca/wp-content/plugins/media-library-plus/im