's on the Hill"], "guid"=>{"__content__"=>"http://www.macleans.ca/?p=672661", "isPermaLink"=>"false"}, "description"=>"<p>In this show taped live at U of O, MPs, Paul Wells and Susan Delacourt preview 2015 in politics</p><p>The post <a href=\"http://www.macleans.ca/politics/ottawa/macleans-on-the-hill-the-first-anniversary-edition/\">Maclean&#8217;s on the Hill: The first anniversary edition</a> appeared first on <a href=\"http://www.macleans.ca\">Macleans.ca</a>.</p>", "encoded"=>"<span itemprop=\"articleBody\" class=\"entry-content\"><p><a href=\"http://www.macleans.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/ON-THE-HILL.jpg\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-514329\" alt=\"podcast\" src=\"http://www.macleans.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/ON-THE-HILL.jpg\" width=\"1600\" height=\"900\" /></a></p>\n<p>Each week, the <em>Maclean\u2019s</em> politics team and Rogers radio\u2019s Cormac Mac Sweeney sit down to hash out the week\u2019s news in Ottawa.</p>\n<p>This week, we celebrated the first anniversary of the podcast with a live taping at the University of Ottawa. (Rough cut and photos: <a href=\"http://www.macleans.ca/news/canada/join-us-for-a-live-taping-of-macleans-on-the-hill/\">here.</a>) We spoke with Conservative minister <strong>Pierre Poilievre,</strong> NDP MP <strong>Jean Crowder,</strong> Liberal MP <strong>Irwin Cotler</strong> and Equal Voice&#8217;s <strong>Nancy Peckford</strong> about what to expect from this year&#8217;s election. Then <strong>Paul Wells</strong> and <strong>Susan Delacourt\u00A0</strong>talked about where federal politics stands with nine months to go.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://itunes.apple.com/ca/podcast/macleans.ca-podcast/id884074529?mt=2\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Subscribe on iTunes today,</strong></a> or play below, on <a href=\"http://www.stitcher.com/podcast/macleans-on-the-hill\" target=\"_blank\">Stitcher</a>.</p>\n<p><iframe src=\"https://w.soundcloud.com/player/?url=https%3A//api.soundcloud.com/tracks/188726750&amp;color=ff5500&amp;auto_play=false&amp;hide_related=false&amp;show_comments=true&amp;show_user=true&amp;show_reposts=false\" height=\"166\" width=\"100%\" frameborder=\"no\" scrolling=\"no\"></iframe></p>\n<h1 style=\"text-align: center;\">THE HEADLINES</h1>\n<ul class=\"block-grid mobile two-up\">\n<li>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://www.macleans.ca/politics/on-iraq-questions-of-combat-cost-and-clarity/\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://www.macleans.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/MAC38_INSIDE_OTTAWA_FEATURE011-300x300.jpg\" width=\"100%\" /> <strong>ON IRAQ</strong></a><br />\n<em style=\"line-height: 19px;\">Where&#8217;s the constructive dialogue?</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://www.macleans.ca/politics/ottawa/patriotism-was-the-last-refuge-of-scoundrels-youtubes-next/\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://www.macleans.ca/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/MAC07_247_FEATURE.jpg\" width=\"100%\" /> <strong>ON CAMPAIGNS</strong></a><br />\n<em style=\"line-height: 19px;\">The PMO bets on security</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://www.macleans.ca/politics/ottawa/why-pm-wont-meet-premiers/\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://www.macleans.ca/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/MAC06_WELLS_FEATURE01.jpg\" width=\"100%\" /> <strong>ON PREMIERS</strong></a><br />\n<em style=\"line-height: 19px;\">Why the PM won&#8217;t meet them</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://www.macleans.ca/politics/justin-trudeau-with-nine-months-to-go/\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://www.macleans.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/MAC18_COSH_FEATURE.jpg\" width=\"100%\" /> <strong>ON TRUDEAU</strong></a><br />\n<em style=\"line-height: 19px;\">Nine month from E-Day</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://www.macleans.ca/politics/ottawa/victims-of-communism-memorial-designs-worried-chief-justice/\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://www.macleans.ca/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/MAC06_VICTIMS_OF_COMMUNISM_T