Trying to understand what happened' /></div>\n<p>Follow Wells on Twitter at <a href=\"https://twitter.com/search?q=inklessPW&amp;src=typd\">@inklessPW</a> for live reports and commentary.</p>\n</span><p>The post <a href=\"http://www.macleans.ca/multimedia/video/video-trying-to-make-sense-of-it-all/\">After three days of bloodshed, Saturday routine</a> appeared first on <a href=\"http://www.macleans.ca\">Macleans.ca</a>.</p>", "commentRss"=>"http://www.macleans.ca/multimedia/video/video-trying-to-make-sense-of-it-all/feed/"}, {"title"=>"Maclean\u2019s on the Hill: Paris, Syria and Julian Fantino", "link"=>"http://www.macleans.ca/politics/ottawa/macleans-on-the-hill-2/", "comments"=>["http://www.macleans.ca/politics/ottawa/macleans-on-the-hill-2/#comments", "0"], "pubDate"=>"Sat, 10 Jan 2015 15:14:45 +0000", "creator"=>"macleans.ca", "category"=>["Ottawa", "Podcast", "Politics", "Maclean's on the Hill"], "guid"=>{"__content__"=>"http://www.macleans.ca/?p=662661", "isPermaLink"=>"false"}, "description"=>"<p>Also on this week's episode, Martin Patriquin talks about press freedom with Ezra Levant </p><p>The post <a href=\"http://www.macleans.ca/politics/ottawa/macleans-on-the-hill-2/\">Maclean&#8217;s on the Hill: Paris, Syria and Julian Fantino</a> appeared first on <a href=\"http://www.macleans.ca\">Macleans.ca</a>.</p>", "encoded"=>"<span itemprop=\"articleBody\" class=\"entry-content\"><a href=\"http://www.macleans.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/ON-THE-HILL.jpg\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-514329\" alt=\"podcast\" src=\"http://www.macleans.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/ON-THE-HILL.jpg\" width=\"1600\" height=\"900\" /></a>\n<p>Each week, the Maclean\u2019s politics team and Cormac MacSweeney sit down to hash out the week\u2019s news in Ottawa. This week, Maclean&#8217;s Political Editor Paul Wells is in Paris to discuss the terror attacks in France, the Maclean&#8217;s Panel talks about the cabinet shuffle that kicked Julian Fantino out of Veterans Affairs, and we celebrate Sir John A Macdonald&#8217;s 200th birthday.\u00A0\u200B</p>\n<p><iframe scrolling=\"no\" frameborder=\"0\" style=\"width:720px;height:180px;border:0;overflow:hidden;\" width=\"842\" height=\"180\" src=\"http://app.stitcher.com/splayer/f/58030/36579044?el=0&#038;refid=stpr\"></iframe></p>\n<h1 style=\"text-align: center;\">THE HEADLINES</h1>\n<ul class=\"block-grid mobile two-up\">\n<li>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://www.macleans.ca/news/world/paris-shooting-in-conversation-with-ezra-levant/\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://www.macleans.ca/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/MAC02_EZRA_LEVANT_THUMBNAIL.jpg\" width=\"100%\" /> <strong>ON CARTOONS</strong></a> <em style=\"line-height: 19px;\">In conversation with Ezra Levant</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://www.macleans.ca/politics/ottawa/lets-talk-about-all-the-possible-results-of-this-years-election/\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://www.macleans.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/shutterstock_78856576-300x300.jpg\" width=\"100%\" /> <strong>ON ELECTIONS</strong></a> <em style=\"line-height: 19px;\">Anything can happen in October</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://www.macleans.ca/politics/ottawa/heres-to-you-john-a//\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://www.macleans.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/MAC01_SIR_JOHN_A_MACDONALD_THUMBNAIL01.jpg\" width=\"100%\" /> <strong>ON JOHN A</strong></a> <em style=\"line-height: 19px;\">The first PM turns 200</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://www.macleans.ca/politics/newsmaker-of-the-day-kevin-vickers-becomes-our-man-in-ireland/\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://www.macleans.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/MAC49_NM_NMOFTHEYEAR_THUMBNAIL01.jpg\" width=\"100%\" /> <strong>ON VICKERS</strong></a> <em style=\"line-height: 19px;\">Canada&#8217;s new man in Ireland</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://www.macleans.ca/politics/ottawa/bernard-valcourt-a-street-fighter-heads-back-to-the-streets/\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://www.macleans.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/MAC01_BERNARD_VALCOURT_FEATURE.jpg\" width=\"100%\" /> <strong>ON VALCOURT</strong></a> <em style=\"line-height: 19px;\">Harper&#8217;s street-fighter</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://www.macleans.ca/politics/ottawa/the-monumental-politics-behind-ottawas-newest-memorials/\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://www.macleans.ca/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/MAC02_SUPREME_COURT_FEATURE.jpg\" width=\"100%\" /> <strong>ON MEMORIALS</strong></a> <em style=\"line-height: 19px;\">Ottawa&#8217;s circuit is bolstered by two</em></p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p><a href=\"http://www.macleans.ca/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/episode46.mp3\">Download the podcast. </a></p>\n</span><p>The post <a href=\"http://www.macleans.ca/politics/ottawa/macleans-on-the-hill-2/\">Maclean&#8217;s on the Hill: Paris, Syria and Julian Fantino</a> appeared first on <a href=\"http://www.macleans.ca\">Macleans.ca</a>.</p>", "commentRss"=>"http://www.macleans.ca/politics/ottawa/macleans-on-the-hill-2/feed/"}, {"title"=>"Elegy for Charlie Hebdo: A silent dispatch from Paris", "link"=>"http://www.macleans.ca/news/world/elegy-for-charlie-hebdo-a-silent-dispatch-from-paris/", "comments"=>["http://www.macleans.ca/news/world/elegy-for-charlie-hebdo-a-silent-dispatch-from-paris/#comments", "0"], "pubDate"=>"Fri, 09 Jan 2015 23:07:41 +0000", "creator"=>"macleans.ca", "category"=>["Video", "World", "Charlie Hebdo", "Paris shooting"], "guid"=>{"__content__"=>"http://www.macleans.ca/?p=663147", "isPermaLink"=>"false"}, "description"=>"<p>Video: In just more than a minute, Maclean's contributor Nick Kozak captures a day like no other in Paris</p><p>The post <a href=\"http://www.macleans.ca/news/world/elegy-for-charlie-hebdo-a-silent-dispatch-from-paris/\">Elegy for Charlie Hebdo: A silent dispatch from Paris</a> appeared first on <a href=\"http://www.macleans.ca\">Macleans.ca</a>.</p>", "encoded"=>"<span itemprop=\"articleBody\" class=\"entry-content\"><p>When the worst seemed over \u2014 20 dead at last count, including three gunmen \u2014 the president of France addressed the nation. &#8220;The threats facing France are not finished,&#8221; he warned. &#8220;We are a free people who cave to no pressure.&#8221;</p>\n<p>Security forces blanketed the city and region Friday as two separate hostage incidents unfolded. And while police were seemingly everywhere, so were Parisians. </p>\n<p>Maclean&#8217;s contributor Nick Kozak captured these images on a day of siege and resilience: </p>\n<div itemprop=\"video\" itemscope itemtype=\"http://schema.org/VideoObject\"><div style=\"display:none\"></div>\n<object id=\"1204075512\" class=\"BrightcoveExperience\"><param name=\"bgcolor\" value=\"#FFFFFF\" />\n<param name=\"wmode\" value=\"transparent\" />\n<param name=\"templateReadyHandler\" value=\"rdm_foundation_bc_onTemplateReady\" />\n<param name=\"templateLoadHandler\" value=\"rdm_foundation_bc_onTemplateLoaded\" />\n<param name=\"includeAPI\" value=\"true\" />\n<param name=\"isVid\" value=\"true\" />\n<param name=\"isUI\" value=\"true\" />\n<param name=\"dynamicStreaming\" value=\"true\" />\n<param name=\"width\" value=\"640\" />\n<param name=\"height\" value=\"360\" /><param name=\"playerID\" value=\"781201057001\" /><param name=\"@videoPlayer\" value=\"3980246879001\" /></object><meta itemprop='name' content='Maclean&#039;s - Elegy for Charlie Hebdo - A silent dispatch from Paris' /><meta itemprop='thumbnail' content='http://newsandbusiness.rogersdigitalmedia.com.edgesuite.net/bcassets/13639244001/201501/2791/13639244001_3989295867001_Day-2.jpg?pubId=13639244001' /><meta itemprop='duration' content='PT1M24S' /><meta itemprop='description' content='Maclean&#039;s - Elegy for Charlie Hebdo - A silent dispatch from Paris' /></div>\n</span><p>The post <a href=\"http://www.macleans.ca/news/world/elegy-for-charlie-hebdo-a-silent-dispatch-from-paris/\">Elegy for Charlie Hebdo: A silent dispatch from Paris</a> appeared first on <a href=\"http://www.macleans.ca\">Macleans.ca</a>.</p>", "commentRss"=>"http://www.macleans.ca/news/world/elegy-for-charlie-hebdo-a-silent-dispatch-from-paris/feed/"}, {"title"=>"The Maclean\u2019s Political Panel: Fantino, O\u2019Toole and a growing cabinet", "link"=>"http://www.macleans.ca/politics/ottawa/the-macleans-political-panel-fantino-otoole-and-a-growing-cabinet/", "comments"=>["http://www.macleans.ca/politics/ottawa/the-macleans-political-panel-fantino-otoole-and-a-growing-cabinet/#comments", "0"], "pubDate"=>"Fri, 09 Jan 2015 22:47:09 +0000", "creator"=>"macleans.ca", "category"=>["Ottawa", "Video", "The Maclean's Politics Panel"], "guid"=>{"__content__"=>"http://www.macleans.ca/?p=663123", "isPermaLink"=>"false"}, "description"=>"<p>Our Ottawa bureau on the stories that mattered this week</p><p>The post <a href=\"http://www.macleans.ca/politics/ottawa/the-macleans-political-panel-fantino-otoole-and-a-growing-cabinet/\">The Maclean&#8217;s Political Panel: Fantino, O&#8217;Toole and a growing cabinet</a> appeared first on <a href=\"http://www.macleans.ca\">Macleans.ca</a>.</p>", "encoded"=>"<span itemprop=\"articleBody\" class=\"entry-content\"><p>Each week, the Maclean\u2019s Ottawa gathers in the OMNI studios to talk about the political stories that matter in the nation&#8217;s capital. This week, they take on Julian Fantino&#8217;s dismissal from veterans affairs, the ever-ballooning federal cabinet, and persistent rumours of a spring election (spoiler alert: the panel is skeptical of a vote before autumn):</p>\n<div itemprop=\"video\" itemscope itemtype=\"http://schema.org/VideoObject\"><div style=\"display:none\"></div>\n<object id=\"990990981\" class=\"BrightcoveExperience\"><param name=\"bgcolor\" value=\"#FFFFFF\" />\n<param name=\"wmode\" value=\"transparent\" />\n<param name=\"templateReadyHandler\" value=\"rdm_foundation_bc_onTemplateReady\" />\n<param name=\"templ