7;s</em>\u00A0Politics Editor Paul Wells reports from Paris on a national day of mourning. A day earlier, 10 journalists and two police officers were gunned down in the offices of Charlie Hebdo, a satirical news weekly. The killers remain at large.</p>\n<p>Follow Wells and his continuing coverage on Twitter at @inklessPW:</p>\n<blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\" lang=\"en\"><p><a href=\"http://t.co/MlEaVk9MyV\">pic.twitter.com/MlEaVk9MyV</a></p>\n<p>\u2014 Paul Wells (@InklessPW) <a href=\"https://twitter.com/InklessPW/status/553239889119309824\">January 8, 2015</a></p></blockquote>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\" lang=\"en\"><p>Place de la R\u00E9publique. <a href=\"http://t.co/0Lb5BNDFkx\">pic.twitter.com/0Lb5BNDFkx</a></p>\n<p>\u2014 Paul Wells (@InklessPW) <a href=\"https://twitter.com/InklessPW/status/553237270116204544\">January 8, 2015</a></p></blockquote>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Related posts:</strong></p>\n<p><a href=\"http://www.macleans.ca/multimedia/photo/photos-mourning-in-the-place-de-la-republique/\">Grief and gathering in Place de la R\u00E9publique</a></p>\n<p><a href=\"http://www.macleans.ca/news/world/satire-demands-moral-courage/\">Satire: Use at own risk\u00A0</a></p>\n<p><a href=\"http://www.macleans.ca/news/world/cartoonists-pay-tribute-to-charlie-hebdo/\">Cartoonists pay tribute to #CharlieHebdo</a></p>\n</span><p>The post <a href=\"http://www.macleans.ca/news/world/video-charlie-hebdo-was-here/\">Paul Wells: &#8216;Charlie Hebdo was here&#8217;</a> appeared first on <a href=\"http://www.macleans.ca\">Macleans.ca</a>.</p>", "commentRss"=>"http://www.macleans.ca/news/world/video-charlie-hebdo-was-here/feed/"}, {"title"=>"Photos: Grief and gathering in Place de la R\u00E9publique", "link"=>"http://www.macleans.ca/multimedia/photo/photos-mourning-in-the-place-de-la-republique/", "comments"=>["http://www.macleans.ca/multimedia/photo/photos-mourning-in-the-place-de-la-republique/#comments", "0"], "pubDate"=>"Thu, 08 Jan 2015