d/noted-on-the-internet-panda-cub-in-the-snow/", "comments"=>["http://www.macleans.ca/news/world/noted-on-the-internet-panda-cub-in-the-snow/#comments", "0"], "pubDate"=>"Wed, 07 Jan 2015 10:39:32 +0000", "creator"=>"The Associated Press", "category"=>["Video", "World", "Bao Bao"], "guid"=>{"__content__"=>"http://www.macleans.ca/?p=660681", "isPermaLink"=>"false"}, "description"=>"<p>Video is melting hearts around the globe.</p><p>The post <a href=\"http://www.macleans.ca/news/world/noted-on-the-internet-panda-cub-in-the-snow/\">Noted on the internet: Panda cub in the snow</a> appeared first on <a href=\"http://www.macleans.ca\">Macleans.ca</a>.</p>", "encoded"=>"<span itemprop=\"articleBody\" class=\"entry-content\"><p><iframe width=\"560\" height=\"315\" src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/HQZ3-OD0ml0\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen></iframe></p>\n<p>WASHINGTON \u2014 A video of The National Zoo&#8217;s panda cub playing in the snow for the first time is melting hearts around the globe.</p>\n<p>The Washington zoo released video of Bao Bao the panda cub rolling downhill in the snow as she played with a block of wood Tuesday. Bao Bao then does a backward somersault and later pounces on her mother, Mei Xiang.</p>\n<p>The video was shared on social media and news sites across the world.</p>\n<p>Though Bao Bao is 16 months old, she didn&#8217;t make her public debut until April, since baby pandas are very small and fragile.</p>\n<p>Bao Bao turned 1 in August. She&#8217;s only the second panda born at the zoo to survive to her first birthday.</p>\n</span><p>The post <a href=\"http://www.macleans.ca/news/world/noted-on-the-internet-panda-cub-in-the-snow/\">Noted on the internet: Panda cub in the snow</a> appeared first on <a href=\"http://www.macleans.ca\">Macleans.ca</a>.</p>", "commentRss"=>"http://www.macleans.ca/news/world/noted-on-the-internet-panda-cub-in-the-snow/feed/"}, {"title"=>"Photo essay: The vivid cabs of Mumbai\u2019s taxiwallahs", "link"=>"http://www.macleans.ca/society/life/mumbais-colourful-cabs/", "comments"=>["http://www.macleans.ca/society/life/mumbais-colourful-cabs/#comments", "0"], "pubDate"=>"Sun, 04 Jan 2015 15:34:59 +0000", "creator"=>"Genna Buck", "category"=>["Life", "Photo", "Mumbai", "photo essay"], "guid"=>{"__content__"=>"http://www.macleans.ca/?p=658147", "isPermaLink"=>"false"}, "description"=>"<p>The flamboyant Padminis and their drivers are fading away </p><p>The post <a href=\"http://www.macleans.ca/society/life/mumbais-colourful-cabs/\">Photo essay: The vivid cabs of Mumbai\u2019s taxiwallahs</a> appeared first on <a href=\"http://www.macleans.ca\">Macleans.ca</a>.</p>", "encoded"=>"<span itemprop=\"articleBody\" class=\"entry-content\"><script type='text/javascript'>var image_max_height = \"500\";</script><script type='text/javascript'>var imagesArray = [{\"id\":657819,\"mlpId\":\"6057\",\"src\":\"http:\\/\\/www.macleans.ca\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2014\\/12\\/MAC01_PHOTO_ESSAY_TAXI011-660x439.jpg\",\"width\":660,\"height\":439,\"medSrc\":\"http:\\/\\/www.macleans.ca\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2014\\/12\\/MAC01_PHOTO_ESSAY_TAXI011-150x150.jpg\",\"medWidth\":150,\"medHeight\":150,\"smallSrc\":\"http:\\/\\/www.macleans.ca\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2014\\/12\\/MAC01_PHOTO_ESSAY_TAXI011-150x150.jpg\",\"smallWidth\":150,\"smallHeight\":150,\"tagSlugs\":\"\",\"tagNames\":\"\",\"title\":\"Road Wallah\",\"caption\":\"\",\"loaded\":false,\"description\":\"(Dougie Wallace)\",\"order\":\"1\",\"imageCount\":\"10\",\"alt\":\"\"}];</script><a name='gallery_top' id='gallery_top'></a><a name='mobile_gallery_top' id='mobile_gallery_top'></a>\n<div id='mlp_ajax_loader'><img src='http://www.macleans.ca/wp-content/plugins/media-library-plus/images/ajax-loader.gif' /></div>\n<div id=\"universal_mlp_container\">\n\n<div id=\"mlp_gallery_viewer\">\n\n\t<div id=\"mlp_nav_image_container\">\n\n\t\t<div id=\"image_container\"></div>\n\t\t<div class=\"mlp_prev_zone mlp_shadow_zone\"></div>\n\t\t<div class=\"mlp_next_zone mlp_shadow_zone\"></div>\n\n\t\t<div class=\"mlp_prev_detector mlp_detector\" id=\"mlp_prev_detector\">&nbsp;</div>\n        <div class=\"mlp_next_detector mlp_detector\" id=\"mlp_next_detector\">&nbsp;</div>\n\n\t\t<div class=\"mlp_prev_zone mlp_arrow_container\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"mlp_inner_nav\">\n\t\t\t\t<a href=\"#\"></a>\n\t\t\t</div>\n\t\t</div>\n\n\t\t<div class=\"mlp_next_zone mlp_arrow_container\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"mlp_inner_nav\">\n\t\t\t\t<a href=\"#\"></a>\n\t\t\t</div>\n\t\t</div>\n\n\t</div>\n    <div id=\"mlp_caption\"><span class=\"mlp_current_caption\"></span></div>\n\n    <div class=\"mlp_mobile_nav show-on-phones\">\n        <div id=\"full-gallery-nav\">\n            <a id=\"mlp_prev_arrow\" class=\"left arrow mlp_arrow_button mlp_prev_arrow\" href=\"#\">&lt;</a>\n            <a id=\"mlp_next_arrow\" class=\"right arrow mlp_arrow_button mlp_next_arrow\" href=\"#\">&gt;</a>\n        </div>\n        <div id=\"full-gallery-numbers\"><span class=\"hide-on-phones\">Photo </span><b><span class=\"mlp_current_page\"></span></b> of <b><span class=\"mlp_total_page\"></span></b></div>\n    </div>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n\n            <div class=\"row\">\n\n                <div id=\"full-gallery-nav\">\n                    <a id=\"mlp_prev_arrow\" class=\"left arrow mlp_arrow_button mlp_prev_arrow\" href=\"#\">&lt;</a>\n                    <div id=\"full-gallery-numbers\"><span class=\"mlp_current_page\"></span> of <span class=\"mlp_total_page\"></span></div>\n                    <a id=\"mlp_next_arrow\" class=\"right arrow mlp_arrow_button mlp_next_arrow\" href=\"#\">&gt;</a>\n                </div>\n\n\n                <div class=\"clear show-on-tablets\"></div>\n                <div class=\"clear show-on-mobiles\"></div>\n\n\n               <div id=\"mlp_info\" class=\"twelve columns\">\n                    <div id=\"full-gallery-title\"><span class=\"mlp_current_title\"></span></div>\n                    <div id=\"full-gallery-desc\">\n                        <span class=\"mlp_current_desc\"></span>\n                    </div>\n                </div>\n            </div>\n            \n<p>Over the course of three years, <a href=\"http://www.dougiewallace.com/\">photographer Dougie Wallace</a> captured Mumbai\u2019s iconic taxi drivers\u2014a vanishing breed\u2014using a little bit of gentle ambush and a very powerful flash. \u201CBasically when they\u2019d stop at the traffic lights, I would just put the camera up to the windshield or shoot through the window at the side. I was like a one-man band,\u201D Wallace says.</p>\n<p><a href=\"http://www.thenational.ae/business/industry-insights/indian-taxis-in-heavy-traffic-as-competition-grows\">Mumbai\u2019s cabbies</a>, or taxiwallahs, have been driving black and yellow Premier Padminis, based on a Fiat design, since the 1960s. But production ceased in 2000, and in 2008 the Mumbai government passed a law banning taxicabs more than 25 years old. Padminis are sturdy, cheap and easy to repair, and thanks to tight regulations on the auto industry, they used to be practically the only taxi on the road. Now they\u2019re falling out of use. As those old cabs disappear, so too will their flamboyant, Bollywood-inspired interiors. To bump and careen around town surrounded by neon zebra stripes, \u201970s \u201Cflower power\u201D-themed upholstery or a garish paisley pattern was once a quintessential Mumbai experience.</p>\n<p>\u201CIt\u2019s not kitsch. Kitsch is the wrong word,\u201D Wallace says. \u201CIt\u2019s not self-conscious.\u201D An old Padmini can be found for the equivalent of US$1,000 or even less, and decorated to the owner\u2019s content. Newer cars, though, run into the thousands\u2014far beyond the budget of the average driver. Many will likely have to leave the trade.</p>\n<p>Since colonial times, cabbies who own their cars have dressed in white, while renters donned a khaki uniform. That\u2019s changing, too: now all drivers, regardless of their status, must wear a crisp white shirt.</p>\n</span><p>The post <a href=\"http://www.macleans.ca/society/life/mumbais-colourful-cabs/\">Photo essay: The vivid cabs of Mumbai\u2019s taxiwallahs</a> appeared first on <a href=\"http://www.macleans.ca\">Macleans.ca</a>.</p>", "commentRss"=>"http://www.macleans.ca/society/life/mumbais-colourful-cabs/feed/"}, {"title"=>"Maclean\u2019s on the Hill: A year-end extravaganza", "link"=>"http://www.macleans.ca/politics/ottawa/macleans-on-the-hill-a-year-end-extravaganza/", "comments"=>["http://www.macleans.ca/politics/ottawa/macleans-on-the-hill-a-year-end-extravaganza/#comments", "0"], "pubDate"=>"Mon, 29 Dec 2014 18:30:33 +0000", "creator"=>"macleans.ca", "category"=>["Ottawa", "Podcast", "Politics", "Maclean's on the Hill"], "guid"=>{"__content__"=>"http://www.macleans.ca/?p=655461", "isPermaLink"=>"false"}, "description"=>"<p>Interviews with David Johnston, Joe Oliver, Stephen Poloz, and David Coletto</p><p>The post <a href=\"http://www.macleans.ca/politics/ottawa/macleans-on-the-hill-a-year-end-extravaganza/\">Maclean&#8217;s on the Hill: A year-end extravaganza</a> appeared first on <a href=\"http://www.macleans.ca\">Macleans.ca</a>.</p>", "encoded"=>"<span itemprop=\"articleBody\" class=\"entry-content\"><div id=\"attachment_517809\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\" style=\"width: 832px\"><a href=\"http://www.macleans.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/MAC_HEADSHOTS_GROUP77-822-story.jpeg\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-517809\" alt=\"John Geddes, Cormac Mac Sweeney, Paul Wells and Aaron Wherry\" src=\"http://www.macleans.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/MAC_HEADSHOTS_GROUP77-822-story.jpeg\" width=\"822\" height=\"462\" /></a><p class=\"wp-caption-text\">John Geddes, Cormac MacSweeney, Paul Wells and Aaron Wherry</p></div>\n<p>Each week, the <em>Maclean\u2019s</em> politics team and Cormac MacSweeney sit down to hash out the week\u2019s news in Ottawa. This week, a special year-end edition of Maclean&#8217;s on the Hill, including interviews with Governor General David Johnston, Bank of Canada Governor Stephen Poloz, Finance Minister Joe Oliver, NDP leader Thomas Mulcair and Liberal leader Justin Trudeau. The <em>Maclean&#8217;s</em> Ottawa bureau looks back on a remarkable year of political and international news\u2014and ahead at an unpredictable election year. Listen to back episodes by <a href=\"https://itunes.apple.com/ca/podcast/macleans.ca-podcast/id884074529?mt=2\">subscribing in iTunes</a>.</p>\n<p><iframe width=\"100%\" height=\"350\" scrolling=\"no\" frameborder=\"no\" src=\"https://w.soundcloud.com/player/?url=https%3A//api.soundcloud.com/playlists/67959189&amp;color=ff5500&amp;auto_play=false&amp;hide_related=false&amp;show_comments=true&amp;show_user=true&amp;show_reposts=false\"></iframe></p>\n<h1 style=\"text-align: center;\">THE HEADLINES</h1>\n<ul class=\"block-grid mobile two-up\">\n<li>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://www.macleans.ca/politics/ottawa/governor-general-david-johnston/\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://www.macleans.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/MAC50_INTERVIEW_FEATURE.jpg\" width=\"100%\" /><br />\n<strong>ON A GG</strong></a><br />\n<em style=\"line-height: 19px;\">A year-ender with David Johnston</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://www.macleans.ca/politics/interview-thomas-mulcair-on-the-environment-taxes-and-trudeau/\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://www.macleans.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/MAC47_POWER_LIST28_THUMB1-300x300.jpg\" width=\"100%\" /><br />\n<strong>ON MULCAIR</strong></a><br />\n<em style=\"line-height: 19px;\">A year-ender with the NDP leader</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://www.macleans.ca/politics/interview-justin-trudeau-on-income-splitting-the-budget-and-the-misconduct-controversy/\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://www.macleans.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/08/MAC34_INTERVIEW_THUMB.jpg\" width=\"100%\" /><br />\n<strong>ON TRUDEAU</strong></a><br />\n<em style=\"line-height: 19px;\">A year-ender with the Liberal leader</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://www.macleans.ca/politics/ottawa/the-pms-latest-secret-weapon-joe-oliver/\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://www.macleans.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/MAC38_JOEOLIVER_FEATURE01.jpg\" width=\"100%\" /><br />\n<strong>ON OLIVER</strong></a><br />\n<em style=\"line-height: 19px;\">A finance minister&#8217;s ascent</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://www.macleans.ca/economy/qa-stephen-poloz-on-jobs-household-debt-and-the-economy/\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://www.macleans.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/MAC46_COSH_THUMBNAIL01.jpg\" width=\"100%\" /><br />\n<strong>ON POLOZ</strong></a><br />\n<em style=\"line-height: 19px;\">The central banker talks economy</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://www.macleans.ca/politics/ottawa/what-our-mps-are-doing-over-the-holidays/\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://www.macleans.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/MAC52_MPSONHOLIDAY_FEATURE011.jpg\" width=\"100%\" /><br />\n<strong>ON HOLIDAYS</strong></a><br />\n<em style=\"line-height: 19px;\">Where are our MPs?</em></p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p><a href=\"http://www.macleans.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/yearend-full.mp3\">Download this podcast</a></p>\n</span><p>The post <a href=\"http://www.macleans.ca/politics/ottawa/macleans-on-the-hill-a-year-end-extravaganza/\">Maclean&#8217;s on the Hill: A year-end extravaganza</a> appeared first on <a href=\"http://www.macleans.ca\">Macleans.ca</a>.</p>", "commentRss"=>"http://www.macleans.ca/politics/ottawa/macleans-on-the-hill-a-year-end-extravaganza/feed/"}, {"title"=>"Video: Discussing our 2014 Newsmakers of the Year", "link"=>"http://www.macleans.ca/multimedia/video/video-discussing-three-of-our-top-2014-newsmakers/", "comments"=>["http://www.macleans.ca/multimedia/video/video-discussing-three-of-our-top-2014-newsmakers/#comments", "0"], "pubDate"=>"Mon, 29 Dec 2014 14:04:52 +0000", "creator"=>"macleans.ca", "category"=>["Canada", "Video", "Newsmakers 2014"], "guid"=>{"__content__"=>"http://www.macleans.ca/?p=657649", "isPermaLink"=>"false"}, "description"=>"<p>Assistant editor Adrian Lee appears on Breakfast Television to discuss some of our picks from our Newsmakers issue, out now</p><p>The post <a href=\"http://www.macleans.ca/multimedia/video/video-discussing-three-of-our-top-2014-newsmakers/\">Video: Discussing our 2014 Newsmakers of the Year</a> appeared first on <a href=\"http://www.macleans.ca\">Macleans.ca</a>.</p>", "encoded"=>"<span itemprop=\"articleBody\" class=\"entry-content\"><p>Assistant editor Adrian Lee dropped by Breakfast Television in Toronto on Monday morning to chat about three of this year&#8217;s 2014 Maclean&#8217;s Newsmakers of the Year, and a bit about how they were chosen. </p>\n<p>The 2014 <em>Newsmakers</em> issue is on newsstands, digital platforms, and Next Issue now.</p>\n<div itemprop=\"video\" itemscope itemtype=\"http://schema.org/VideoObject\"><div style=\"display:none\"></div>\n<object id=\"490007253\" class=\"BrightcoveExperience\"><param name=\"bgcolor\" value=\"#FFFFFF\" />\n<param name=\"wmode\" value=\"transparent\" />\n<param name=\"templateReadyHandler\" value=\"rdm_foundation_bc_onTemplateReady\" />\n<param name=\"templateLoadHandler\" value=\"rdm_foundation_bc_onTemplateLoaded\" />\n<param name=\"includeAPI\" value=\"true\" />\n<param name=\"isVid\" value=\"true\" />\n<param name=\"isUI\" value=\"true\" />\n<param name=\"dynamicStreaming\" value=\"true\" />\n<param name=\"width\" value=\"640\" />\n<param name=\"height\" value=\"360\" /><param name=\"playerID\" value=\"781201057001\" /><param name=\"@videoPlayer\" value=\"3963880905001\" /></object><meta itemprop='name' content='Maclean&#039;s names Newsmakers of the Year' /><meta itemprop='thumbnail' content='http://citynews.rogersdigitalmedia.com.edgesuite.net/images/593482582001/201412/2873/593482582001_3963924140001_thumbnail-for-video-3964050761001.jpg?pubId=593482582001' /><meta itemprop='duration' content='PT4M36S' /><meta itemprop='description' content='Maclean&#039;s assistant editor Adrian Lee drops by Breakfaat Television to discuss who the magazine named on their  Newsmakersof the Year list and how they decide who&#039;s in.' /></div>\n<h4>Our Newsmakers of the Year:</h4>\n<p><a href=\"http://www.macleans.ca/news/newsmakers-of-the-year-kevin-vickers-reluctant-hero/\" target=\"_blank\">Kevin Vickers, the reluctant hero</a><br />\n<a href=\"http://www.macleans.ca/news/newsmaker-janet-yellen/\" target=\"_blank\">Janet Yellen, the central banker with the human touch</a><br />\n<a href=\"http://www.macleans.ca/news/canada/newsmakers-lucy-decouterereva-seth/\" target=\"_blank\">Lucy DeCoutere and Reva Seth, rallying figures</a><br />\n<a href=\"http://www.macleans.ca/news/newsmaker-ebola/\" target=\"_blank\">Ebola, a modern plague</a></p>\n</span><p>The post <a href=\"http://www.macleans.ca/multimedia/video/video-discussing-three-of-our-top-2014-newsmakers/\">Video: Discussing our 2014 Newsmakers of the Year</a> appeared first on <a href=\"http://www.macleans.ca\">Macleans.ca</a>.</p>", "commentRss"=>"http://www.macleans.ca/multimedia/video/video-discussing-three-of-our-top-2014-newsmakers/feed/"}, {"title"=>"Year in Pictures: Celebrations and commemorations", "link"=>"http://www.macleans.ca/multimedia/photo/year-in-pictures-celebrations-and-commemorations/", "comments"=>["http://www.macleans.ca/multimedia/photo/year-in-pictures-celebrations-and-commemorations/#comments", "0"], "pubDate"=>"Thu, 25 Dec 2014 16:19:43 +0000", "creator"=>"Andrew Tolson", "category"=>"Photo", "guid"=>{"__content__"=>"http://www.macleans.ca/?p=656285", "isPermaLink"=>"false"}, "description"=>"<p>From colourful festivals to victory cheers, these were the celebrations that stood out to us this year</p><p>The post <a href=\"http://www.macleans.ca/multimedia/photo/year-in-pictures-celebrations-and-commemorations/\">Ye